commit.message:
Avoid lambda in hookcall path

PluginManager adds an adapter lambda to the hook call path. This adds
overhead and makes the stack trace more messy.

Change the call convention such that the adaptation is not needed, and
remove the lambda.
Don't include setup overhead in benchmark measurement

Optimize argument check in _HookCaller.__call__

This check is quite expensive, try to reduce its overhead.

Remove redundant set() on dict keys view

A dict keys view supports set-like operations.

commit.message:
Initialize HookCaller._call_history to None instead of using hasattr

hasattr is slow, can't be typed properly, and makes the code harder to
understand.

Add missing `self` to method in test

I don't think it was the intention to omit it.
Remove explicit inheritance from object
Remove redundant str() in _formatdef

Remove varnames() caching

varnames() is only used when creating hookspecs and hookimpls, so it's
not in any hot path. So caching it is a net negative.
Remove unset _HookCaller.{argnames,kwargnames}
